A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 1 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to motor carriers, so as to exempt ride share drivers or ride share network services
3 from the definition of motor carrier; to provide for definitions; to revise legislative findings;
4 to exempt ride share network services from liability for actions of ride share drivers in certain
5 instances; to provide for conforming changes; to provide for related matters; to repeal
6 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Article 3 of Chapter 1 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
10 motor carriers, is amended in Code Section 40-1-100, relating to definitions relative to
11 certification of motor carriers, by revising paragraphs (6) and (12) as follows:
12 "(6) 'Department' means the Department of Public Safety 'Elderly or disabled passenger'
13 means an individual over the age of 60 years or who, by reason of illness, injury, age,
14 congenital malfunction, or other permanent or temporary incapacity or disability, is
15 unable to utilize mass transportation facilities as effectively as an individual who is not
16 so affected."
