59 SECTION 2.
60 Said article is further amended by revising Code Section 40-1-191, relating to legislative
61 findings, preemption, and ride share network service, transportation referral service,
62 transportation referral service provider, and taxi service doing business at a county or
63 municipal airport, as follows:
64 "40-1-191.
65 The General Assembly finds that it is in the public interest to provide uniform
66 administration and parity among ride share network services, transportation referral
67 services, and transportation referral service providers, including taxi services, that operate
68 in this state for the safety and protection of the public. The General Assembly fully
69 occupies and preempts the entire field of administration and regulation over ride share
