70 network services, ride share drivers, transportation referral services, transportation referral
71 service providers, and taxi services as governed by this part; provided, however, that the
72 governing authority of any county or municipal airport shall be authorized to regulate any
73 ride share network service, ride share driver, transportation referral service, transportation
74 referral service provider, and taxi service consistent with the process used for limousine
75 carriers, as set forth in Code Section 40-1-162, who are doing business at any such airport
76 and may establish fees as part of such regulation process; provided, further, that such fees
77 shall not exceed the airport's approximate cost of permitting and regulating ride share
78 network services, ride share drivers, transportation referral services, transportation referral
79 service providers, and taxi services; and provided, further, that such governing authorities
80 of such airports shall accept a for-hire license endorsement or private background check
81 certification pursuant to Code Section 40-5-39 as adequate evidence of sufficient criminal
82 background investigations and shall not require any fee for any further criminal
83 background investigation; and provided, further, that local governments may maintain
84 certificates of public necessity and convenience and medallion requirements and company
85 requirements for taxi services as provided in this part and may establish maximum fares
86 for taxi services. The list of ride share network services, transportation referral services,
87 transportation referral service providers, and taxi services on the public website of the
88 department shall be sufficient evidence that such services have licenses issued by the
89 department."
90 SECTION 3.
91 Said article is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
92 "40-1-201.
93 (a) No ride share network service shall be liable under any theory of liability, including,
94 but not limited to, vicarious or product liability, for any injury to persons or damage to
95 property from the operation of a personal passenger car by a ride share driver by reason of
